Executive Profile
Barbara Jean Samardzich  Chief Operating Officer and Vice President, Ford Of Europe GmbHAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships58--
Background

		Ms. Barbara Jean Samardzich, also known as Barb, served as an Executive Officer of Ford Motor Co. since September 1, 2016 until October 1, 2016. Ms. Samardzich served as the Chief Operating Officer and Vice President of Ford of Europe of Ford Motor Company since November 1, 2013 until September 1, 2016. Ms. Samardzich was responsible for many of Ford of Europe's operations, including manufacturing, quality, product development, purchasing, sustainability, environment ... and safety engineering. She served as Vice President of Product Development for Ford of Europe GmbH from September 1, 2011 to November 1, 2013. She was responsible for all Product Development activities in the European region and lead Ford's Global Vehicle Engineering, Noise Vibration and Harshness and Global Vehicle Evaluation and Verification teams. She served as Vice President of Global Product Programs at Ford Of Europe GmbH since January 2011. She has held several key leadership roles in Ford’s Product Development organization. Ms. Samardzich served as Vice President of Powertrain Engineering at Ford Of Europe GmbH until December 31, 2010, responsible for engine and transmission engineering worldwide. She served as Vice President of Powertrain Operations - Americas Division of Ford Of Europe GmbH. since October 2005. Ms. Samardzich served as an Executive Director of Lifestyles/Youth Vehicles of Ford Of Europe GmbH since October 2002. She was responsible for the design, engineering and development of nine key Ford and Lincoln vehicles, including the 2005-model Mustang. She served as Chief Engineer for the Automatic Transmission Engineering Operations of Ford from January 2000 to October 2002. She served as Chief Engineer for F-Series commercial trucks at Ford. She served as Quality Director for the Small and Medium Vehicle Center of the European operations of Ford from March 1999 to January 2000. She served various positions in the Powertrain division of Ford from September 1990 to December 1998. Prior to joining Ford in 1990, she served various engineering, sales and marketing positions in the Thermal Design Engineer for Commercial Nuclear Fuel Division of Westinghouse Electric Corporation from 1981 to 1990. She has been a Director of SKF AB since March 29, 2017. She has been an Independent Director of Adient plc since October 31, 2016. She served as a Director of Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS since December 10, 2013 until October 12, 2016. She serves as a Director of Ford Sollers Holding LLC. Ms. Samardzich served as a Director at MTS Systems Corporation since 2001 until June 6, 2017. She serves on the boards of several universities and non-profit organizations. Her work in automatic transmissions and her experience in product creation won her the "Women in Engineering Achievement" award from Design News in 2004. She was named amongst the Top 50 Automotive Women by Automobilwoche for 2011. Before being named an Automotive News All Star for 2009 and 2010, she was acknowledged as one of the Most Influential Women by Crain's Detroit Business in 2007. She received the Distinguished Women Award from Northwood University in 2006. And she was named a Leading Woman in the North American Automotive Industry by Automotive News in 2005 and 2010. Ms. Samardzich holds a Bachelor of Science in Mechanical Engineering from the University of Florida (USA), a Master of Science in Mechanical Engineering from Carnegie Mellon University and Master's in Engineering Management from Wayne State University (USA).Read Full Background




